The paper deals with algorithms and their analysis, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on the Lovasz Local Lemma and its applications suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The mention of entropy estimation suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible sub-category. The mention of bad events and dealing with super-polynomially many bad events suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of stochastic local search algorithms suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
